8
[h3 id=Introduction 
	" Introduction
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"This is Maxim all bosses run of Castlevania: Harmony of Dissonance.
	$LF
	"I performed a drastic reconstruction of the route and saved 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=McBobX's current run|href=/2548M)
	" by a lot of frames with that (due to the difference of emulators, we can't compare their movie lengths exactly though).
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=Objective 
	" Objective
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" Emulator used: BizHawk 1.11.6.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Starts from SRAM.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Uses warps.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Aims for fastest time.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Aims to defeat all bosses.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Abuses glitches.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 id=AboutTheRun 
	" About the run
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=DefinitionOfTheGoal 
	" Definition of the goal
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"To set flags of destruction of all bosses ($000358, EWRAM domain).
	$LF
	"We can make a judgement of it with the hatchway to Dracula Wraith's room.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=EmulatorAndCoreSelection 
	" Emulator and core selection
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"I used BizHawk with mGBA core instead of common VBA to make this run. I think VBA is also okay for now, but BizHawk is seems to be better than VBA in terms of future TASing. That's why I chose BizHawk. As you know, BizHawk supports two cores for GBA emulation: VBA-next and mGBA. It's embarrassing, but I really don't know which core is suitable for CVHoD, so I selected the new one (mGBA) for the present.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=MakingTheSram 
	" Making the SRAM
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Due to the change of emulator, there's need to make a SRAM to start this run. I made 
	[a href=https://onedrive.live.com/redir?resid=DAFF8007E8BFD7A1!254&authkey=!AGzp095pqhJf1ys&ithint=file%2cbk2 rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"a semi-TAS movie
	]a
	" at first.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=LuaScriptsUsed 
	" Lua scripts used
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"I edited Robert_Ordis's lua scripts so as to be available on BizHawk environment and integrated some further functions. It can be downloaded 
	[a href=https://onedrive.live.com/redir?resid=DAFF8007E8BFD7A1!255&authkey=!ACWIr0WKuKUVXFo&ithint=file%2czip rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"here
	]a
	". The original scripts can be found in 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=his submission|href=/4067S)
	".
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=HistoryOfTheBranch 
	" History of the branch
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"After the publication of current run, several works have been done in Japanese community (nicovideo). However, most works have not been reported to oversea communities, including TASVideos, I guess. So I'll show history about this "Maxim, all bosses" branch including in-bounds run as reference.
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Yuzuhara3SMaximInBoundsIn113995ReleasedOn20110811 
	" 
	[a href=http://www.nicovideo.jp/watch/sm15279275 rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Yuzuhara_3's "Maxim, in-bounds" in 11:39.95 (released on 2011/08/11)
	]a
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"It improves Comicalflop & zggzdydp's initial in-bounds run by 2037 frames. He succeeded to construct the new route which doesn't require door-warp glitch.
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]div
